          <text>
            Streamwalker settled and said,
            "Good walking today. You handled the challenge well."

            Brightbloom replied,
            "Very well! Tomorrow's our last day together—we'll reach the boundary by afternoon, meet the Territory Three guides! It'll be wonderful but also sad—I always get attached to travelers—"

            Streamwalker said,
            "Brightbloom."

            Brightbloom continued,
            "Right, staying positive! It'll be wonderful! New guides, new territory, your journey continuing! That's good!"

            I pull off my boot and dump out the swamp water.
            I say, "It is good—different, but good, and *I mean it*."

            Different guides every few days—new challenges in every territory—temporary teams that form, work, and then end.
            But the journey continues, and I am learning to continue with it.

            ¶

            _One swamp hole at a time._
          </text>
